cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper discusses data stream processing frameworks and their performance impact, which is closely related to database systems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper evaluates the performance of three different streaming frameworks, which are all distributed systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the impact of an abstraction layer on the performance of data stream processing systems, which is related to algorithm design and optimization. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper presents a novel benchmark architecture for comparing the performance impact of using Apache Beam on different streaming frameworks, which is related to software engineering practices. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper evaluates the performance impact of using an abstraction layer on data stream processing systems, which is directly related to performance evaluation.
